# Koi Engine — example environment variables
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are all OPTIONAL. The engine reads them straight from the process
# environment (it does not load a .env file itself), so set them inline, e.g.:
#
#     KOI_MAX_FRAMES=120 ./build/koi-engine
#
# This file documents what's available.

# Render exactly this many frames and then exit cleanly, instead of running
# until the user quits. Useful for headless smoke tests / CI. Unset = run until
# the window is closed or Esc is pressed.
KOI_MAX_FRAMES=

# Render ONE frame into the given image file (BMP) and exit immediately, instead
# of opening the live loop. This is the visual-debugging capture: it saves exactly
# what the engine draws, no screen recording needed. Convert to PNG if you like:
#     sips -s format png out.bmp --out out.png        (macOS)
# Example:  KOI_CAPTURE=/tmp/frame.bmp ./build/koi-engine
KOI_CAPTURE=
